It seems like I have a conversation like this one at least once a week:
Them: &ldquo;Hey Major, you&rsquo;re a pretty nerdy guy, what server distro do you use?&rdquo;
Me: &ldquo;I use CentOS 4 right now.&rdquo;
Them: &ldquo;CentOS? Why not use something more cutting edge, like Fedora or Gentoo?&rdquo;
Me: &ldquo;Well, I like those, but Plesk works really well with CentOS.&rdquo;
Them: &ldquo;Seriously? You use Plesk? WHY?&rdquo;
My CentOS server hosts a fair amount of domains for people I know and people I don&rsquo;t know.
